         <img height="333" src="depot/images/astro-2017-08-03-desl.jpg" width="599"/>
        </div>
        <div id="abstract">
         <div class="title">
          "Dark Energy Survey reveals most precise measure of universe's structure", UChicago News
         </div>
         <div class="subtitle">
          PFC@KICP in the News: August 3, 2017
         </div>
         <div class="text">
          "These first major cosmology results are a tribute to the many people who have worked on the project since it began 14 years ago," said Dark Energy Survey Director
          <a href="http://cosmos.uchicago.edu/people/index.php#joshua-frieman">
           Josh Frieman
          </a>
          , a PFC co-Investigator. "It was an exciting moment when we unveiled the results to ourselves just last month, after carrying out a 'blind' analysis to avoid being influenced by our prejudices."
          <br/>
          <br/>
          A map of dark matter covering about one -- thirtieth of the entire sky and spanning several billion light years -- red regions have more dark matter than average, blue regions less dark matter.
          <br/>
          <i>
           Courtesy of
           <a href="http://cosmos.uchicago.edu/people/fellows.php#chihway-chang">
            Chihway Chang
           </a>
           , the DES collaboration.
          </i>
         </div>
         <div class="www">
          <a href="http://cosmos.uchicago.edu/news/innews.php#innews560">
           Learn more &gt;&gt;
          </a>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
